<p><i><b><span lang="de" xml:lang="de">Das Kapital: Kritik der politischen Ökonomie</span></b></i> (<small>IPA</small>:&#160;<span title="Pronunciation in IPA" class="IPA"><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:IPA" title="Wikipedia:IPA">[das kapiˈtaːl]</a></span>) (<i><b>Capital</b></i>, in the English translation) is an extensive <a href="/wiki/Treatise" title="Treatise">treatise</a> on <a href="/wiki/Political_economy" title="Political economy">political economy</a> written in <a href="/wiki/German_language" title="German language">German</a> by <a href="/wiki/Karl_Marx" title="Karl Marx">Karl Marx</a> and edited in part by <a href="/wiki/Friedrich_Engels" title="Friedrich Engels">Friedrich Engels</a>. The book is a critical analysis of <a href="/wiki/Capitalism" title="Capitalism">capitalism</a>. Its first volume was published in 1867.</p>
